    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect Lmax calculation causing SSB detection failures\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_Lmax` function in `nr_parms.c` contained incorrect logic for determining the maximum number of SS/PBCH blocks per half-frame. The previous implementation applied a 2.4 GHz frequency threshold for TDD configurations with SSB type C, which violates 3GPP TS 38.213 Section 4.1 specifications. This caused downstream protocol state machine transitions to fail during SSB detection and cell search procedures.\n\nThis fix corrects the Lmax calculation to follow the specification directly based on frequency range without special case handling for TDD or specific SSB types.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/nr_parms.c`: Simplified `set_Lmax` function logic to remove incorrect conditional checks and follow 3GPP specification directly\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain TDD band configurations with SSB type C, the gNB would incorrectly calculate Lmax using a 2.4 GHz threshold instead of the standard 3.0 GHz threshold. This led to:\n1. Incorrect SSB pattern detection\n2. Failed cell search procedures\n3. UE unable to establish RRC connection due to missing SIB1\n\nThe issue was observable when running NR-UE with band n78 TDD configuration where SSB detection would fail during initial cell search.\n"
}